===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈɡaː(ɹ).dən/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"gA:(r)d@n/

===Etymology===
From Old Northern French ''gardin'', a variant of Old French [[jardin]], a diminutive of [[jart]], borrowed from Old Franconian ''*gard'', from Germanic ''*garda-'' (Old English [[geard|ȝeard]]).

===Noun===
'''garden'''
# A decorative place outside-usually where plants are grown for food (''vegetable garden'') or ornamental purposes (''flower garden'').
# The front or back of a house.
# ''slang,'' pubic hair

